<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="II"><UNDER>AFFIDAVIT</UNDER></TI>
<P>I, <BOLD>JOHN HILPERT</BOLD>, of Vancouver, British Columbia, private investigator, SWEAR (OR AFFIRM) THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am a private investigator retained by the plaintiff, Rong Wei, and as such have knowledge of the matters hereinafter referred to save and except where stated to be based on information and belief and where so stated, I veriiy believe same to be true.</P>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Introduction</EM></TI>
<P>2. On or about November 16, 2016, I was hired by Ms. Wei to look into Allan Chiu to verify his identity and certain claims he had made to Ms. Wei regarding his past.</P>
<P>3. Ms. Wei provided me with the name Allan Chiu and that she believed him to be 58 years of age. Additionally, Ms. Wei provided information on Mr. Chiu's spouse, Mui Kwan Queenie LAU, by providing a copy of her BC driver's license, which provided her date of birth as XXXXXXXXXX XXXXXXXXXX.</P>
<P>4. I used the above information to verify that Mr. Chiu's full name is Allan SungFai Chiu and that his date of birth is XXXXXXXXXX.</P>
<P>5. I used these particulars in the course of my investigation to confirm whether records referencing the name &ldquo;Allan Chiu&rdquo; were referring to the individual that was the subject of my investigation.</P>
<P>6. Through my investigations, I also confirmed that Mr. Chiu currently resides at XXXXXXXXXX XXXXXXXXXX.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Mr. Chiu's Education Background</EM></TI>
<P>7. I understood from Ms. Wei that Mr. Chiu advised her that he had a Bachelor of Commerce from the Sauder School of Business at the University of British Columbia and a Masters of Business Administration from Brown University. As a result, I contacted the Sauder School of Business and Brown University in an effort to try to verify this information.</P>
<P>8. On November 28, 2016, I was advised by a representative of the Sauder School of Business that while it had a record of an Allan Chiu attending the school from 1974 to 1979, its records did not match Mr. Chiu's full name or date of birth.</P>
<P>9. On November 25, 2016, I was advised by the Admissions and Alumni Office of Brown University that it had searched its records from 1975 to 1985 and that it was unable to confirm that an Allan S. Chiu born in XXXXXXXXXX had attended the school as an under graduate or graduate student.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Goldman Sachs</EM></TI>
<P>10. I further understood from Ms. Wei that Mr. Chiu had advised her that he had previously worked in a high level management role for Goldman Sachs in its Asia divisions. Specifically, I understood that Mr. Chiu had said he worked for Goldman Sachs in Singapore between 1985&ndash;1997 and Hong Kong from 1998&ndash;2008.</P>
<P>11. On or about November 29, 2016 I contacted several Asian division branches of Goldman Sachs and made inquiries about Mr. Chiu. Additionally, i researched and inquired with current Investment Analysts with publicly listed previous work histories to Goldman Sachs and their Asian divisions.</P>
<P>12. I was unable to confirm with Goldman Sachs or anyone previously working for their Asian divisions that anyone named Allan Chiu had worked for or been associated to Goldman Sachs or any of its equity investment divisions.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Stoneset Equity</EM></TI>
<P>13. Ms. Wei had also advised me that she had been informed by Mr. Chiu that he had previously lived in Calgary, Alberta and been employed with Temasek Private Holdings Ltd.</P>
<P>14. During the course of my investigation, I could not find any association or employment between Temasek Private Holdings Ltd. and Mr. Chiu.</P>
<P>15. During the course of my investigation, I found that Mr. Chiu's last employment was with Stoneset Asia Equities (&ldquo;<BOLD>Stoneset Equities</BOLD>&rdquo;). It is my understanding that Stoneset Asia Equities is part of the Stoneset group of companies (collectively, &ldquo;<BOLD>Stoneset</BOLD>&rdquo;).</P>
<P>16. During the course of my Investigation, I additionally confirmed that Ms. Lau was also last employed with Stoneset Equities as a translator.</P>
<P>17. As part of my investigations, I made inquiries about Mr. Chiu with a confidential informant within the private equity trade whose initials are P.S. As a private investigator, it is my practice not to name confidential informants without their permission to do so, as I need to maintain good relationships with my confidential informants so that they will provide me with information in the future. In this case, P.S. has not given me permission to name him.</P>
<P>18. I asked P.S., who has access to personal information, to assist in identifying Mr. Chiu and his employment with Stoneset Equities. I consider P.S. to be a reliable source, because I have worked with P.S. in the past and have found the information he has provided me in the past to be reliable. I am also aware that P.S. has experience working with oil and gas projects in Alberta and that he would be knowledgeable about the investment community in Alberta.</P>
<P>19. I provided P.S. with Mr. Chiu's personal details and a recent photograph. P.S. advised me that he had known an individual by the name of Allan Chiu from Calgary who matched the photograph I provided.</P>
<P>20. P.S. advised me that the individual he knew had been involved in a major equities scandal in Calgary around 2011 and further advised me that the scandal had involved a real estate investment scheme, which proved to be a Ponzi scheme.</P>
<P>21. P.S. also stated that he was not aware of any disciplinary action that had been taken against Mr. Chiu. P.S. stated he believed that Mr. Chiu had lost money himself and for his investors in the scheme, and that Mr. Chiu had since retired to stay away from the backlash of potential prosecution.</P>
<P>22. I was also able to locate an online news article from the Montreal Gazette, which discussed some of the allegations against one of the Stoneset companies. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>A</BOLD>&rdquo; to this affidavit is a copy of an online news article from the Montreal Gazette, which discusses Stoneset.</P>
<P>23. I also conducted a search of Alberta Investors Protection's website and found an article entitled &ldquo;Calgary Investigation reveals Alberta Investors protection;&rdquo; which referred to Stoneset Equities. I cannot recall if the article was posted directly on Alberta Investors Protection's website or whether the website had a link to the article, but I printed out a copy of the article. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>B</BOLD>&rdquo; to this affidavit is a copy of the article I printed out entitled &ldquo;Calgary Investigation reveals Alberta Investors protection;&rdquo;</P>
<P>24. Stoneset Equities is also listed on Alberta Investors Protection's website under the heading &ldquo;Alberta EMD Failed/Failing Investments&rdquo;. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo; to this affidavit is a copy of a print out from Alberta Investors Protection's website.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Allan Chiu Consulting</EM></TI>
<P>25. During the course of my investigations, I determined that Mr. Chiu had been holding himself out as operating a business under the name Allan Chiu Consulting.</P>
<P>26. I located a URL for a website for Allan Chiu Consulting, which was <UNDER>www.allanchiuconsulting.asia</UNDER>. I was able to determine that this URL address had an active website from 2009 to March 2016. The URL address remained active and owned by Mr. Chiu until March 2017.</P>
<P>27. Mr. Chiu had listed the business address for Allan Chiu Consulting as a PO Box located in Hong Kong.</P>
<P>28. An additional address and phone number listed in Calgary, Alberta confirmed the URL to belong to Allan Chiu, the subject of my investigation.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Royal Bank Debt</EM></TI>
<P>29. As part of my investigation, I conducted a limited credit and asset inquiry for Mr. Chiu and Mui Lau.</P>
<P>30. The results of this inquiry disclosed that Mr. Chiu had an outstanding debt of $34,000 owed to the Royal Bank. The results of the debt inquiry indicated that the Royal Bank attempted collection actions against Mr. Chiu for the debt and had since written off the debt as a bad debt in 2014.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Mui Kwan Queenie Lau</EM></TI>
<P>31. As a part of my investigation, I also arranged for property searches to be conducted in the United Kingdom for the name Mui Kwan Queenie Lau.</P>
<P>32. The results of these searches came back negative. The search results did provide a number of variances on the name Mui Kwan Queenie Lau, but none of these variances appeared to match Ms. Lau.</P>
<P><TABLE>
<SGMLTBL>
<TBLBODY TBLWD="600">
<TBLCDEFS COLSEP="VDOT" HALIGN="LEFT" CHARPOS="75%" TOPSEP="HDOT">
