<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="III"><UNDER>AFFIDAVIT</UNDER></TI>
<P>I, <BOLD>RONG (ELIZA) WEI</BOLD>, of Vancouver, British Columbia, housewife, SWEAR (OR AFFIRM) THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am the plaintiff in this action and as such have knowledge of the matters hereinafter referred to save and except where stated to be based on information and belief and where so stated, I verily believe same to be true.</P>
<P>2. On May 12, 2017, my counsel filed a Notice of Civil Claim in this matter.</P>
<P>3. I swear this affidavit in support of my application for an order permitting me to serve the Notice of Civil Claim and my application for a Mareva injunction on the Defendants, Allan Chiu (&ldquo;<BOLD>Chiu</BOLD>&rdquo;) and Mui Kwan Queenie Lau also known as Mui Kwan Queenie Chiu (&ldquo;<BOLD>Lau</BOLD>&rdquo;) by alternative means.</P>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Defendants' Residence</EM></TI>
<P>4. I have known Chiu and Lau since 2014.</P>
<P>5. During that time, Chiu told me that he and Lau lived at XXXXXXXXXX XXXXXXXXXX (the &ldquo;<BOLD>Birney Property</BOLD>&rdquo;). Initially, Chiu told me that he and Lau owned the Birney Property, but I now understand that they rented the property.</P>
<P>6. In or about February 2017, I visited both Chiu and Lau at the Birney Property.</P>
<P>7. Subsequently, I understood from Chiu that Lau was no longer living at the Birney Property. Chiu also told me that he does not know where Lau is.</P>
<P>8. At this time, I have no information regarding the whereabouts of Lau.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Attempts to Serve Defendants</EM></TI>
<P>9. As stated in my first affidavit, made May 12, 2017, I had previously made plans to meet Chiu on May 14, 2017 at which time he had promised to return to me USD$70,000 of the money I had provided to Chiu and Lau, but on May 12, Chiu called me to cancel that meeting.</P>
<P>10. I have not received any communications from Chiu since May 12, 2017. Chiu also did not transfer any funds to me on May 15, 2017.</P>
<P>11. Also as stated in my first affidavit, during my conversation with Chiu on May 12, 2017, Chiu told me that he was staying with relatives in Richmond. I do not believe that Chiu was telling me the truth when he said he was staying in Richmond, because he has told me so many lies during our relationship.</P>
<P>12. On May 12, 2017, I went to the Birney Property at approximately 10:45 pm in an effort to try to serve Chiu with the Notice of Civil Claim. There was no indication that anyone was home at the Birney Property and the Defendants' car was not in their parking spot.</P>
<P>13. The next day, May 13, 2017, I want to the Birney Property twice at approximately 8:00 am and 11:10 pm. At those times, there was no indication that anyone was home at the Birney Property and the Defendants' car was not in their parking spot.</P>
<P>14. Subsequently, on May 14, 2017, at approximately 12:20 pm, I went to the Birney Property to try to serve Chiu with the Notice of Civil Claim. Once again, there was no indication that anyone was at home and the Defendants' car was not in their parking spot.</P>
<P>15. The following day, May 15, 2017, at approximately, 8:25 am, I went again to the Birney Property to try to serve Chiu with the Notice of Civil Claim. On that visit, I knocked on the front door to the Birney Property, but no one answered. There was no indication that anyone was home and I again observed that the Defendants' car was not in their parking spot. I also looked around the Defendants' neighborhood to try to locate their car, but I could not find it.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Defendants' Contact Information</EM></TI>
<P>16. As set out in my first affidavit, made May 12, 2017, during my involvement with Chiu, he used the following email address to communicate with me: <UNDER>allan@allanchiuconsulting.asia</UNDER></P>
<P>17. Chiu and I also frequently communicate by WeChat. Chiu's WeChat username is: AllanC1001. Chiu also provided me with his cellphone number, which XXXXXXXXXX.</P>
<P>18. I believe that if a copy of the Notice of Civil Claim was emailed to Chiu at the above email address, he would receive the Notice of Civil Claim. This is particularly the case if a WeChat message was sent to Chiu advising him that the Notice of Civil Claim had been sent to his email account.</P>
<P>19. At one point, Chiu also provided me with the following email address to communicate with him and advised me that this email address was a shared email address used by Lau, as as himself: XXXXXXXXXX.</P>
<P>20. In addition, Lau and I communicate by WeChat. Lau's WeChat username is: QueenieC1001.</P>
<P>21. Lau also provided me with her cellphone number, which is XXXXXXXXXX. I have tried calling Lau's cellphone number to arrange a meeting to serve her with the Notice of Civil Claim, but she did not pick up my call and the call did not go to voicemail.</P>
<P>22. I believe that if a copy of the Notice of Civil Claim was emailed to Lau at the above email address and a WeChat message was set to Lau advising her that the Notice of Civil Claim had been emailed, she would receive the Notice of Civil Claim.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Chiu's use of Cash</EM></TI>
<P>23. When I travelled with Chiu to different places, he would bring large amounts of cash with him and used cash to pay for things.</P>
<P>24. Chiu told me that for tax reasons he did not always deposit his money into a bank account. At one time, Chiu recommended to me that I not keep my money in a bank account and instead keep it in a safe or safety deposit box.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>TD Bank Account</EM></TI>
<P>25. In or around February 2017, I met with Chiu and he showed me what he said was a summary of my investments.</P>
<P>26. On the back of the summary was banking information for Chiu or Lau from TD Bank. I wanted to keep the summary of my investments, but Chiu told me I could not keep the summary and took the paper from me. He said this was because the paper had personal information on the back.</P>
<P>27. Because of the TD Bank banking information I saw, I believe that Chiu, Lau or both of them have a bank account with TD Bank.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Scotiabank Account</EM></TI>
<P>28. Earlier this year, I went to see a movie with Chiu at Cineplex. At that time, Chiu used a SCENE card.</P>
<P>29. It is my understanding that the SCENE card is a rewards program linked to Scotiabank.</P>
<P>30. For this reason, I believe that Chiu may also have a bank account with Scotiabank.</P>
