<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="II">AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, <BOLD>JOHN HILPERT</BOLD>, private investigator, of XXXXXXXXXX, MAKE OATH AND SAY AS FOLLOWS:</P>
<P>1. I am a private investigator retained by the plaintiff, Rong Wei, and as such have personal knowledge of the facts deposed to in this affidavit except where stated to be on information and belief and in which case I verily believe them to be true.</P>
<P>2. As I explained in my Affidavit #1 dated May 12, 2017, I was hired by Ms. Wei in November 2016 to look into the defendant Allan Chiu to verify his identity and certain claims he had made to Ms. Wei regarding his past. Ms. Wei provided me with photographs of Mr. Chiu. Ms. Wei also provided me with a copy of the defendant Mui Kwan Queenie Lau's driver's licence that had a photograph of Ms. Lau.</P>
<P>3. Using the photographs and other information I obtained concerning Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau, I was able to track their whereabouts and conduct surveillance. During my surveillance, I also observed a young woman frequently accompanying Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau.</P>
<P>4. I took several photographs of Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau in November 2016 as part of my surveillance. I also took several photographs of the young woman accompanying them. When I showed the photographs to Ms. Wei, she confirmed that the individuals in my photographs were Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau, and that the young woman was their daughter Romie.</P>
<P>5. In September 2018, I was asked to conduct further surveillance of Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau in Vancouver, British Columbia and the surrounding area. I was able to track Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau in Vancouver and the surrounding area on several days in September and October, including on September 24, 26, 27 and 28 and October 10, 2018.</P>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>September 24, 2018</EM></TI>
<P>6. On September 24, 2018 at approximately 3: 55 p.m., I observed Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau exit from a black BMW with licence plate number XXXXXXXXXX (the &ldquo;<BOLD>BMW</BOLD>&rdquo;) at the McArthurGlen outlet mall in Richmond, British Columbia. I later observed Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau returning to the BMW and driving away. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit are copies of a series of photographs taken by me on September 24, 2018, along with notes of my observations, which are true.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>September 26, 2018</EM></TI>
<P>7. On the afternoon of September 26, 2018, I observed Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau playing tennis together at outdoor tennis courts at the University of British Columbia (UBC).</P>
<P>8. After they finished playing tennis, Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau returned to the BMW. Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau placed their tennis racquets in the back of the car before departing the area.</P>
<P>9. I followed Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau to a park located on Birney Avenue in the University Endowment Lands. Mr. Chiu exited the BMW and went for a walk with a dog that had been in the vehicle. Ms. Lau stayed with the vehicle, cleaning items out of the trunk.</P>
<P>10. At approximately 3: 30 p.m., Ms. Lau walked to a nearby park located at Webber Lane and Birney Avenue. Ms. Lau took the dog for a walk.</P>
<P>11. Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau returned to the BMW and departed together at approximately 3: 50 p.m. I followed Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau, Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau drove into Richmond, where I observed them shopping, including at Lansdowne Centre, a shopping mall located at 5300 No. 3 Road. At approximately 6: 20 p.m., Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau pulled up to the Lansdowne skytrain station in Richmond. I observed Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau's daughter Romie approach the BMW from the station and enter the vehicle.</P>
<P>12. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit are copies of a series of photographs taken by me on September 26, 2018, along with notes of my observations, which are true.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>September 27, 2018</EM></TI>
<P>13. At approximately 3: 15 p.m. on September 27, 2018, I observed the BMW parked in the 4400 Block of West 10<SUP>th</SUP> Avenue in Vancouver, British Columbia. Ms. Lau and her daughter Romie exited the vehicle and entered the Point Grey Medical Clinic located at 4448 West 10<SUP>th</SUP> Avenue. Mr. Chiu initially remained in the vehicle.</P>
<P>14. At approximately 4: 00 p.m., Mr. Chiu entered the Point Grey Medical Clinic. I was able to do a close-up inspection of the licence plate details of the BMW and observed that the BMW was displaying an insurance tag with an expiry date of September 18, 2018.</P>
<P>15. At approximately 4:44 p.m., Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau exited the medical clinic and returned to the BMW. I then followed Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau as they drove through the UBC area before heading back to the Point Grey Medical Clinic. At approximately 4:59 p.m., Romie exited the clinic alone and entered the rear passenger position of the BMW. The BMW departed once Romie entered the vehicle.</P>
<P>16. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit are copies of a series of photographs taken by me on September 27, 2018, along with notes of my observations, which are true.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>September 28, 2018</EM></TI>
<P>17. At approximately 12: 45 p.m. on September 28, 2018, I observed the BMW parked in front of the IDA University Pharmacy located at 5754 University Blvd on the UBC campus.</P>
<P>18. At approximately 12: 51 p.m., I observed Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau enter the BMW and depart. I followed the BMW to the UBC sports facilities area.</P>
<P>19. At approximately 1: 00 p.m., I observed the BMW parked at the same tennis courts I observed it at on September 26, 2018.</P>
<P>20. At approximately 1: 14 p.m., I observed Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau playing tennis together.</P>
<P>21. At approximately 2: 52 p.m., I observed Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau depart the tennis courts together in the BMW and pick up their daughter Romie. I then followed the BMW to Richmond, where Ms. Lau and Romie were dropped off at the McArthurGlen outlet mall.</P>
<P>22. At approximately 5: 10 p.m., I observed the BMW entering the underground parking to the Ora building located at 6951 Elmbridge Way in Richmond. I observed Mr. Chiu, Ms. Lau and Romie entering the building. The dog that I had observed Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau walking on September 26, 2018 remained in the BMW.</P>
<P>23. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;D&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit are copies of a series of photographs taken by me on September 28, 2018, along with notes of my observations, which are true.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>October 10, 2018</EM></TI>
<P>24. At approximately 4: 30 p.m. on October 10, 2018, I observed Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau shopping at the Costco wholesale store located at 9151 Bridgeport Road in Richmond. I observed that Mr. Chiu was wearing a Cartier watch. I also observed the BMW and noted that the vehicle now displays a new 2019 insurance sticker. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;E&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit are copies of two photographs taken by me on October 10, 2018, along with notes of my observations, which are true.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>The BMW</EM></TI>
<P>25. As part of my initial investigation into Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau in November 2016, I conducted Personal Property Registry searches for both Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau. My search of Ms. Lau uncovered a filing of a PPSA Security Agreement registered by BMW Canada Inc. against Ms. Lau as the base debtor for a 2016 BMW X6 with a serial number of XXXXXXXXXX. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;F&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is a copy of my PPRS Search Result.</P>
<P>26. On April 12, 2018, I conducted a further Personal Property Registry search for Ms. Lau. My search uncovered a filing of a PPSA Security Agreement registered by BMW Canada Inc. against Ms. Lau as the base debtor for a 2017 BMW X4 with a serial number of XXXXXXXXXX. That is the serial number of the BMW with licence plate number XXXXXXXXXX that I observed Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau driving in September and October 2018.</P>
<P>27. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;G&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is a copy of my PPRS Search Result.</P>
