<BLOCK1><TI>APPLICATION RESPONSE</TI>
<P><BOLD>Application response of:</BOLD> The Application Respondents, Allan Chiu and Mui Kwan Queenie Lau (the &ldquo;Defendants&rdquo;)</P>
<P>THIS IS A RESPONSE TO the Notice of Application of the Plaintiff, Rong Wei, dated December 5, 2018.</P>
<BLOCK2 LABEL="Part"><N>1:</N><TI>ORDERS CONSENTED TO</TI>
<P>The Application Respondent consents to the granting of the Orders set out in the following paragraphs of Part 1 of the Notice of Application on the following terms:</P>
<P>1. NIL.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2 LABEL="Part"><N>2:</N><TI>ORDERS OPPOSED</TI>
<P>The Application Respondent opposes the granting of the Orders set out in paragraphs 1 through 3 of Part I of the Notice of Application.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2 LABEL="Part"><N>3:</N><TI>ORDERS ON WHICH NO POSITION IS TAKEN</TI>
<P>The Application Respondent takes no position on the granting of the orders set out in paragraphs NIL of Part 1 of the Notice of Application.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2 LABEL="Part"><N>4:</N><TI>FACTUAL BASIS</TI>
<P>1. For the purposes of this application only, the Application Respondents accept the facts stated at paragraphs 9 and 10.</P>
<P>2. With respect to paragraphs 4 through 5, the Defendants admit the claim of the Plaintiff is as represented but deny the allegations.</P>
<P>3. In the spring of 2016, Queenie Lau was aware of an intimate relationship involving the plaintiff and her husband. As a result of this information and the ongoing nature of the relationship involving the plaintiff and her husband, in April 2017, Ms. Lau was contemplating separation and undertook the process of delivering all funds that were in any way related to the relationship involving the plaintiff and her husband.
<P1>Affidavit #2 of Queenie Lau, at paras. 4&ndash;6.</P1></P>
<P>4. On April 10, 2017, Queenie Lau transferred the sum of $50,000 USD out of the CIBC account to Allan Chiu's Standard Chartered account in Singapore.
<P1>Affidavit #2 of Queenie Lau, at paras. 4(a).</P1></P>
<P>5. On April 12, 2017, Queenie Lau transferred the sum of $120,000 USD out of the CIBC account to Allan Chiu's Standard Chartered account in Singapore.
<P1>Affidavit #2 of Queenie Lau, at paras. 4(b).</P1></P>
<P>6. On May 10, 2018, the Defendants travelled to Hong Kong. Queenie Lau was contemplating the status of the relationship and considering a separation. Allan Chiu travelled with his wife with the intention of reconciling and salvaging the marriage.
<P1>Affidavit #2 of Queenie Lau, at para, 8.</P1>
<P1>Affidavit #3 of Allan Chiu, at para.5.</P1></P>
<P>7. On May 12, 2017, the Plaintiff filed the Notice of Civil Claim in this matter.</P>
<P>8. On May 14, 2017, unaware of the claim that had been filed by the plaintiff, Queenie Lau transferred $175,000USD to Allan Chiu's Bank of China (HK) account in Hong Kong.
<P1>Affidavit #2 of Queenie Lau, at paras. 4(c).</P1></P>
<P>9. On May 16, 2017, unaware of the claim that had been filed by the plaintiff, Queenie Lau transferred $100,000USD to Allan Chiu's Bank of China (HK) account in Hong Kong.
<P1>Affidavit #2 of Queenie Lau, at paras. 4(d)</P1></P>
<P>10. On May 16, 2017, Master Scarth, on appearance by the plaintiff without notice to the defendants, made an order such that the plaintiff was at liberty to serve a copy of the Notice of Civil Claim by sub-service by leaving a copy of the Notice of Civil Claim and the Sub-Service Order at the defendants residence, by e-mailing the defendants, and by sending a WeChat message.</P>
<P>11. On May 16, 2017 at 5:15 pm Pacific Standard Time (&ldquo;<BOLD>PST</BOLD>&rdquo;), which is May 17, 2017 at 8:15am Hong Kong Time (&ldquo;<BOLD>HKT</BOLD>&rdquo;), Gail Major, on behalf of the plaintiff, delivered the Order of Master Scarth, Notice of Civil Claim, Requisition for Short Notice, Notice of Application for a Mareva Order (returnable May 18, 2017 at 9:45am PST), and three supporting affidavits. Mr. Chiu did not recognize the sender and did not open this e-mail.
<P1>Affidavit #3 of Tina Le, Exhibit A, pg. 2</P1>
<P1>Affidavit #3 of Allan Chiu at para. 17</P1></P>
<P>12. On May 19, 2017 at 3:04 pm PST, which was May 20, 2017 at 6:04 am HKT, the Mareva Order was delivered in the second e-mail of Gail Major. Having seen the words &ldquo;Order&rdquo; in the subject line, Mr. Chiu determined it was appropriate to talk to legal counsel. However, as it was Friday near the close of business when he received the e-mail, he was only able to briefly talk to counsel. Jef Poulsen, who advised him to forward the relevant documents to him.
<P1>Affidavit #3 of Allan Chiu at paras. 18-19.</P1></P>
<P>13. On May 19, 2017 between 5:21 pm and 5:39 pm PST, which was May 20, 2017 between 8:21am and 8:39am HKT, Allan Chiu forwarded the e-mail of Gail Major dated May 19, 2017 at 3:04 pm to Jef Poulsen. Allan Chiu did not forward the first e-mail of Gail Major dated May 16, 2017 at 5:15 pm to Jef Poulsen.
<P1>Affidavit #3 of Allan Chiu at paras. 20&ndash;24 &amp; Exhibit A.</P1></P>
<P>14. At some time on May 20, 2017, Mr. Chiu read the Mareva Order but did not understand the terms.
<P1>Affidavit #3 of Allan Chiu at paras. 21</P1></P>
<P>15. On May 21, 2017 at 10:15 am HKT, which was May 20, 2017 at 7:15 pm PST, Allan Chiu messaged the plaintiff on WeChat to request that she withdraw the freezing order.
<P1>Affidavit #3 of Allan Chiu at paras. 22</P1></P>
<P>16. On May 23, 2017 at 9:27 am PST, which was May 24, 2017 at 12:27am HKT, Allan Chiu e-mailed Mr. Poulsen. In the body of the e-mail, Allan Chiu requested that he and his wife wished to retain Mr. Poulsen to represent them. Mr. Chiu advised of the time difference and informed of a &ldquo;response deadline&rdquo; to the court order of May 25, 2017, which Mr. Chiu stated represented 7 days from Thursday, May 18.
<P1>Aff&ic;davit #3 of Allan Chiu at paras. 23</P1></P>
<P>17. On May 23, 2017 at 2:30pm PST, which was May 24, 2017 at 5:30am HKT, Jef Poulsen requests copies of the Application and Affidavits in support of the Mareva Order.\
<P1>Affidavit #3 of Allan Chiu, Exhibit A.</P1></P>
<P>18. On May 24, 2017 at approximately 3:00 pm PST, which was May 25, 2017 at a pproximately 6:00 am HKT, Mr. Chiu and Ms. Lau were first able to talk to legal counsel.
<P1>Affidavit #3 of Allan Chiu at paras. 25</P1></P>
<P>19. In summary, the salient facts with respect to information received from the plaintiff and his ability to contact legal counsel are as follows:
