<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, Mui Kwan Queenie Lau, presently with no permanent address but with an address for service in this matter of 700-595 Burrard Street, Vancouver British Columbia, SWEAR THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am the wife of the Co-Defendant Allan Chiu and am a personally named defendant in these proceedings and, as such, have personal knowledge of the facts and matters set out herein to this Affidavit, except where the same are stated to be on information and belief and, as to those matters, I verily believe them to be true.</P>
<P>2. I was never personally advised of the scheduled examination for discovery scheduled in Vancouver for September 27, 2018. As such, I was unaware of any expectation or obligation to attend the scheduled examination for discovery.</P>
<P>3. In or about August 2018, my biological brother Kwan Ying Lau, advised me that he was diagnosed with stage 4 lung cancer. My brother is presently receiving treatment in the People's Republic of China (&ldquo;<BOLD>China</BOLD>&rdquo;) where he receives treatment for his diagnosis of cancer. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is a true copy of a report provided to me by my brother dated September 21, 2018. The report has been redacted to remove symptomology that is private but contains a summary of the diagnosis, in Chinese and in English, and which specifically reads that he has an invasive carcinoma of the left lobe of his lung. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is a photograph of prescription drugs provided to my brother Kwan Ying Lau for Tagrisso. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is a true copy of summary of a summary of the drug Tagrisso published by drugs.com which was sourced from the internet on December 4, 2018 at https://www.drugs.com/tagrisso.html.</P>
<P>4. In or about January, 2018, my biological mother, advised me that she was diagnosed with gall bladder problems which required frequent hospital visits, including hospitalization in or about February, 2018 for approximately 4 weeks, during which she required surgery to places tents in her bile duct. My mother's health continues to deteriorate. In or about July, 2018, we were advised that she required another surgery. On or about October 25, 2018, my mother underwent another operation to remove stents and removal of her gall bla dder.</P>
<P>5. I verily believe that my mother's health is deteriorating.</P>
<P>6. My mother receives treatment in Hong Kong. I personally do not have ready access to a report to provide as an exhibit.</P>
<P>7. I have been diagnosed with Thalessimia and an anemic condition which has had a greater impact on my health in the last approximately 18 months. I continue to suffer symptoms and receive treatment related to my medical issues.</P>
<P>8. I am not medically trained but believe it to be true that Thalessimia is a blood disorder characterized by decreased hemoglobin and fewer red blood cells than normal. Attached and marked as &ldquo;<BOLD>Exhibit D</BOLD>&rdquo; to my affidavit is a true copy of a summary of Thalassemia by the Mayo Clinic, a non-profit academic medical center based in Rochester, Minnesota, which can be found on the internet at https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/thalassemia/symptomscauses/syc-20354995.</P>
<P>9. The combination of my own health concerns in conjunction with the health issues of my brother and mother has been a constant source of stress, concern, and worry since I became aware of their issues.</P>
<P>10. On or about November 16, 2018, I was advised by my husband, Allan Chiu, of the issues arising from my failure to attend the scheduled Examination for Discovery. Alland advised me that he did not inform me of the scheduled Examination for Discovery as he was concerned for my own well-being.</P>
<P>11. I am able to attend an Examination for Discovery between the dates of December 18, 2018 to December 20, 2018 and will attend whether ordered, or in response to an Appointment to Examine for Discovery.</P>
<P>12. I swear this affidavit in response to the Notice of Application of the plaintiff in the above referenced action regarding orders for contempt of court, to strike out my Response to Civil Claim, to attend discovery, provide document disclosure, and related orders pertaining to costs.</P>
