<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="III"><UNDER>AFFIDAVIT</UNDER></TI>
<P>I, Allan Chiu, retired businessman, with no permanent address but with a service address at 700-595 Burrard Street, Vancouver, BC SWEAR THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am a Defendant in this Action and, as such, I have personal knowledge of the matters stated herein except where such matters are stated to be based on information and belief, in which case I believe those matters to be true.</P>
<P>2. I am the husband of the Defendant Mui Kwan Queenie Chiu (&ldquo;Mrs. Chiu&rdquo;), and have been since 2002.</P>
<BLOCK2><TI><UNDER>AFFIDAVIT OF JOHN HILPERT</UNDER></TI>
<P>3. I have read the Affidavit #1 of John Hilpert sworn herein May 12, 2017 (the &ldquo;Hilpert Affidavit&rdquo;).</P>
<P>4. In response to paragraphs 3 and 4 of the Hilpert Affidavit, I was bom in Hong Kong on XXXXXXXXXX My full name is Allan Sung Fai Chiu.</P>
<P>5. In response to paragraph 6 of the Hilpert Affidavit, I have been resident in Canada since 2010 and, since 2013, my principal residence had been at XXXXXXXXXX. In August 2018, I have had no permanent residence and have been residing with family.</P>
<P>6. In response to paragraphs 7 through 9 of the Hilpert Affidavit, I never told the Plaintiff that I had attended either the University of British Columbia or Brown University. My only discussions with the Plaintiff about universities was with respect to which universities she might consider for her son. I did not attend either the Un iversity of British Columbia or Brown University as a student.</P>
<P>7. In response to paragraphs 10 through 12 of the Hilpert Affidavit, I never told the Plaintiff that I had worked for or with Goldman Sachs in either of its Hong Kong or Singapore offices. I did truthfully tell the Plaintiff that I personally knew some individuals who had worked in those offices at the times when I lived in Hong Kong and Singapore respectively. I truthfully told the Plaintiff that I had run my own business while living in Singapore, prior to my retirement in 2010, due to poor health.</P>
<P>8. In response to paragraphs 13 and 14 of the Hilpert Affidavit, I did truthfully tell the Plaintiff that I had lived in Calgary prior to moving to Vancouver but I did not tell her that I had been employed by Temasek Private Holdings Ltd. nor did I ever work for a company of that or similar name.</P>
