<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="IV">AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, Mui Kwan Queenie Lau, presently with no permanent address but with an address for service in this matter of 700-595 Burrard Street, Vancouver British Columbia, SWEAR THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am the wife of the Co-Defendant Allan Chiu and am a personally named defendant in these proceedings and, as such, have personal knowledge of the facts and matters set out herein to this Affidavit, except where the same are stated to be on information and belief and, as to those matters, I verily believe them to be true.</P>
<P>2. The native language I speak is Cantonese. I have a basic grasp of the English language. The contents of this, my affidavit, has been explained to me by my counsel and with the assistance of Serene Chow, a Cantonese speaking lawyer at Boughton Law. Following the explanation, I advise that I understand the information contained in this affidavit as written in English.</P>
<P>3. In the fall of 2015, I was aware that the plaintiff and my husband were meeting quite frequently and I started to be suspicious as to the nature of their relationship.</P>
<P>4. By the spring of 2016, I knew the plaintiff and my husband were in an intimate relationship and more confirmation came when they started to travel on trips together.</P>
<P>5. I knew that funds contained in my CIBC account in Vancouver were somehow related to the relationship between my husband and the plaintiff. I was aware that Allan was assisting the plaintiff in some capacity with trading but I did not know all of the details, purpose of the transactions, or the sources of the funds.</P>
<P>6. Beginning in April 2017, I was seriously considering separating from my husband. I determined that I did not want the funds that were related to the relationship between my husband and the plaintiff in my CIBC account. I transferred the funds from my CIBC account and delivered them to my husband's accounts. As such, I made four transactions to transfer funds:
<P1>(a) On April 10, 2017, I transferred the sum of $50,000 USD to my husband's Standard Chartered account in Singapore. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is my CIBC Account Statement for April 1, 2017 to April 30, 2017. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is the bank record for the transfer of $50,000 on April 10, 2017. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is a branch copy of the transfer of $50,000 USD to my husband's Standard Chartered Account in Singapore;</P1>
<P1>(b) On April 12, 2017, I transferred the sum of $120,000 USD to my husband's Standard Chartered account in Singapore. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;D&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is the bank record for the transfer of $120,000 USD on April 12, 2017. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;E&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is a branch copy of the transfer of $120,000 USD to my husband's Standard Chartered Account in Singapore;</P1>
<P1>(c) On May 15, 2017 PST, I transferred the sum of $175,000 USD to my husband's Bank of China (HK) account in Hong Kong. At the time, I was in Hong Kong and on May 16, 2017 at 12:04am HKT, which was May 15, 2017 at 9:04 am PST, I delivered a fax to my CIBC branch at University Boulevard Banking Centre to provide my instructions. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;F&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is my CIBC Account Statement for May 1, 2017 to May 18, 2017. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;G&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is the bank record for the transfer of $175,000 on May 15, 2017. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;H&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is a branch copy of the transfer of $175,000 USD to my husband's Bank of China (HK) Account in Hong Kong. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;I&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is copy of my instructions to CIBC; and</P1>
<P1>(d) On May 17, 2017 PST, I transferred the sum of $100,000 USD to my husband's Bank of China (HK) account in Hong Kong. At the time, I was in Hong Kong and on May 17, 2017 at 11:46 pm HKT, which was May 17, 2017 at 8:46 am PST, I delivered a fax to my CIBC branch at University Boulevard Banking Centre to provide my instructions. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;J&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is the bank record for the transfer of $100,000 on May 17, 2017. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;K&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is copy of my instructions to CIBC.</P1></P>
<P>7. I was not aware of pending litigation against my husband or myself at the time I made the transfers referenced above.</P>
<P>8. On May 10, 2017, I travelled to Hong Kong as I continued to be unsure of whether I wished to maintain my relationship with my husband. I returned to Vancouver on September 10, 2017.</P>
<P>9. I recall that my husband advised me of the lawsuit against me one or two days before a telephone conference call with Jef Polsen on May 25, 2017 at approximately 6:00 am HKT. This was the first time I became aware of the lawsuit filed against me.</P>
<P>10. I swear this affidavit in response to the Notice of Application of the plaintiff in the above referenced action dated December 5, 2018.</P>
