<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="VI">AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, <BOLD>SERENE CHOW</BOLD>, lawyer, of 700 - 595, Burrard Street, Vancouver, British Columbia, SWEAR THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am a lawyer with the firm Boughton Law Corporation, counsel for the Defendants, Allan Chiu and Mui Kwan Queenie Lau also known as Mui Kwan Queenie Chiu, in this proceeding and as such have personal knowledge of the facts and matters set out herein except where stated to be on information and belief and where so stated I verily believe to be true.</P>
<P>2. I was born and raised in Hong Kong and am fluent in Cantonese.</P>
<P>3. On December 12, 2018, I attended a meeting with the defendant Mui Kwan Queenie Lau also known as Mui Kwan Queenie Chiu (&ldquo;Ms. Lau&rdquo;).</P>
<P>4. Shaun Driver advised me, and I believe it to be true, that Ms. Lau has a basic grasp of the English language but that she is fluent in Cantonese.</P>
<P>5. At the meeting of December 12, 2018, I reviewed the Affidavit #2 of Mui Kwan Queenie Lau (&ldquo;the Affidavit&rdquo;), which was written in English, and I explained the terms of the Affidavit to Ms. Lau in Cantonese, line by line.</P>
<P>6. After explaining the terms of each line of the Affidavit, I confirmed with Ms. Lau that she understood the contents.</P>
<P>7. I am satisfied that she understood the Affidavit and I was present when she swore the Affidavit.</P>
<P>8. Attached to this my affidavit as <BOLD>Exhibit A</BOLD> is a copy of the Affidavit which I reviewed and explained to Ms. Lau.</P>
