<P>I, <BOLD>SARAH CULVER,</BOLD> of 700 - 595, Burrard Street, Vancouver, British Columbia, SWEAR THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am a Legal Administrative Assistant with the firm Boughton Law Corporation, counsel for the Defendants in this proceeding, Allan Chiu and Mui Kwan Queenie Lau also known as Mui Kwan Queenie Chiu, and as such have personal knowledge of the facts and matters set out herein except where stated to be on information and belief and where so stated I verily believe them to be true.</P>
<P>2. On December 7, 2018, I prepared the letter of Shaun Driver addressed to the Branch Manager or Legal Counsel of Scotiabank, 510 Burrard Street, Vancouver, which letter was provided to the defendants for delivery by hand to Scotiabank at the aforesaid location. Attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of the letter of Shaun Driver which I prepared and which was provided to the defendants for delivery by hand to Scotiabank.</P>
<P>3. On December 7, 2018, I prepared the letter of Shaun Driver addressed to the Branch Manager or Legal Counsel of the Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce, 1036 West Georgia Street, Vancouver, which letter was provided to the defendants for delivery by hand to the Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce at the aforesaid location. Attached hereto and ma rked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of the letter of Shaun Driver which I prepared and which was provided to the defendants for delivery by hand to the Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce.</P>
<P>4. On December 7, 2018, I prepared the letter of Shaun Driver addres sed to the Branch Manager or Legal Counsel of TD Canada Trust, 1055 Dunsmuir Street, Vancouver, which letter was provided to the defendants for delivery by hand to the TD Canada Trust at the aforesaid location. Attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of the letter of Shaun Driver which I prepared and which was provided to the defendants for delivery by hand to TD Canada Trust.</P>
<P>5. On December 7, 2018, I sent via fax the letter of Shaun Driver, also of December 7, 2018, to the Bank of China, Tower Branch, 1 Garden Road, Hong Kong, at the number 011-852-2804-6370. On December 7, 2018, at 6:32 p.m., I received by e-mail a confirmation of successful fax transmission to 011-852-2804-6370. Attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;D&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of the letter I faxed to the Bank of China, Tower Branch, and a true copy of the confirmation of successful fax transmission to 011 -852-2804-6370 which I received by e-mail.</P>
<P>6. On December 7, 2018, I sent via fax the letter of Shaun Driver, also of December 7, 2018, to the Standard Chartered Bank (HK) Ltd., GPO Box 23, Hong Kong, at the number 011&mdash;852-2535-4282. On December 7, 2018, at 6:34 p.m., I received by e-mail a confirmation of successful fax transmission to 011-852-2535-4282. Attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;E&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of the letter I faxed to the Standard Chartered Bank (HK) Ltd., and a true copy of the confirmation of successful fax transmission to 011-852-2535-4282 which I received by e-mail.</P>
<P>7. On December 7, 2018, at 12:23 p.m., I sent via e-mail the letter of Shaun Driver, also of December 7, 2018, to BMW Canada Inc. (customerservice@bmw.ca). As of the date this my affidavit is made, I have not received a notification of delivery failure regarding the e-mail I sent to BMW Canada Inc. Attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;F&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of the e-mail I sent to BMW Canada Inc. and a true copy of its enclosure.</P>
<P>8. On December 12, 2018, at 11:53 a.m., I sent via e -mail the letter of Shaun Driver, also of December 12, 2018, to Scotiabank, UBC Branch representatives Kevin Ma XXXXXXXXXX and Peony Lo (XXXXXXXXXX) As the date my affidavit is made, I have not received a notification of delivery f ailure regarding the e-mail I sent to Kevin Ma and Peony Lo. Attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;G&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of the email I sent to Kevin Ma and Peony Lo of Scotiabank, UBC Branch, and a true copy of its enclosure.</P>
<P>9. On December 12, 2018, at 11:57 a.m., I sent via e-mail the letter of Shaun Driver, also of December 12, 2018, to the Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce representative Doreen Middlecoat (XXXXXXXXXX). As of the date this my affidavit is made, I have not received a notification of delivery failure regarding the e-mail I sent to Doreen Middlecoat. Attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;H&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of the e-mail I sent to Doreen Middlecoat of the Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce, and a true copy of its enclosure.</P>
<P>10. On December 17, 2018, I sent by courier to the offices of McEwan Cooper Dennis, LLP, at 900&mdash;980 Howe Street, Vancouver, the partially-executed Order Made After Application of Mr. Justice Grauer of December 4, 2018 (&ldquo;the Order&rdquo;), bearing the sole signature of Shaun Driver. Attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;I&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of the Order and a true copy of the waybill of the courier by which I sent the Order, PDX Courier Service, and which was submitted December 17, 2018, at 3:53:19 p.m.</P>
<P>11. On December 17, 2018, at 1:35 p.m., our office received an e-mail from counsel for the plaintiff attaching the draft Order Made After Application of Mr. Justice Grauer of December 4, 2018. Attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;J&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of the e-mail from counsel for the plaintiff.</P>
<P>12. I am advised by Shaun Driver, and verily believe it to be true, that on December 17, 2018, at 10:06 a.m. he placed a telephone call to Tina Le, paralegal for Craig Dennis, QC, advising, amongst other things, that documents required for the Amended List of Documents have not been provided and Mr. Driver requested an opportunity to speak to Mr. Dennis in anticipation of the need for an application to amend or vary the Order of Mr. Justice Grauer dated December 4, 2018.</P>
<P>13. I am advised by Shaun Driver, and verily believe it to be true, that on December 17, 2018, at 1:23 p.m. he placed a telephone call to Craig Dennis, QC, advising, amongst other things, that documents required for the Amended List of Documents have not been provided. Mr. Driver advised Mr. Dennis of Mr. Driver's intention to bring an application on short leave to amend or vary the Order of Mr. Justice Grauer dated December 4, 2018.</P>
