<P>8. On May 16, 2017, Master Scarth, on appearance by the plaintiff without notice to the defendants, made an order such that the plaintiff was at liberty to serve a copy of the Notice of Civil Claim by sub-service by leaving a copy of the Notice of Civil Claim and the Sub-Service Order at the defendants residence, by e-mailing the defendants, and by sending a We Chat message.</P>
<P>9. On May 16, 2017 at 5:15 pm Pacific Standard Time (&ldquo;<BOLD>PST</BOLD>&rdquo;), which is May 17, 2017 at 8:15 am Hong Kong Time (&ldquo;<BOLD>HKT</BOLD>&rdquo;), Gail Major, on behalf of the plaintiff, delivered the Order of Master Scarth, Notice of Civil Claim, Requisition for Short Notice, Not ice of Application for a Mareva Order (returnable May 18, 2017 at 9:45am PST), and three supporting affidavits.</P>
<P>10. On or about May 23 or 24, 2017, Ms Lau recalls that her husband advised her of the lawsuit one or two days before a telephone conference call with Jef Polsen on May 25, 2017 at approximately 6:00 am HKT. This was the first time she became aware of the lawsuit.
