<P1>(b) Regarding the May 29, 2017 transfer of funds into the account by &ldquo;CIBC WMIS&rdquo; in the amount of $154,000 and out of the account by a &ldquo;Preauthorized Debit&rdquo;, I advise that I was in Hong Kong at the time. Attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> to my Affidavit are boarding passes demonstrating that I was not in Canada at the time of the transaction.</P1>
<P1>(c) On February 12, 2019, I attempted to call CIBC at their toll free number at 1-800-465-2422 to ask CIBC about the nature of the transaction. I was advised that there is a &ldquo;restriction message&rdquo; and they could not disclose information. I have been advised and verily believe it to be true that my lawyer, Shaun Driver, has delivered an e-mail and attempted to call Sabrina DiGiacomo, CIBC Legal Department Law Clerk, to request particulars about the transactions.</P1>
<P1>(d) Regarding the June 8, 2017 transfer of funds from the CIBC US Dollar Account XXXXXXXXXX (the &ldquo;<BOLD>CIBC US Account</BOLD>&rdquo;), plaintiff counsel and Bill Riley, counsel for me at the time, arranged on my instruction for my share of $25,000 in legal fees to be paid from the CIBC Investor's Edge Account #XXXXXXXXXX (&ldquo;<BOLD>CIBC IE Account</BOLD>&rdquo;). Attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of correspondence as between counsel and the Litigation Clerk for CIBC regarding the transaction.</P1>
<P1>(e) Regarding the June 28, 2017 transfer of funds from both the CIBC US Account and the CIBC Account #XXXXXXXXXX (&ldquo;<BOLD>CIBC Account</BOLD>&rdquo;), I arranged through my counsel that $3,500. representing the amount I was permitted to use under the Order, to be applied to my TD Visa and CIBC USD Visa. The matter is referenced in Exhibit B.</P1>
<P1>(f) Regarding the July 27, 2017 transfer of funds, as immediately above, I requested through my counsel that the $3,500, representing the amount I was permitted to use under the Order be applied to my credit cards. I am aware that the request was referenced in an email by my counsel on June 27, 2017 as contained in Exhibit B but do not have access to records to confirm the authority was granted.</P1></P>
<P>6. In August 2017, I did not use any of the $3,500 permissible for living expenses.</P>
