<P>10. In November 2017, the total at Schedule &ldquo;B&rdquo; of the Notice of Application is incorrect. Schedule &ldquo;B&rdquo; has a total of $15,189.49. On review of the calculation and by adding the amounts listed, the total amount is $9,785.59.</P>
<P>11. On or about November 6, 2017, $3,100.00 was deducted from by CIBC account (XXXXXXXXXX). These funds were requested by Kieran Siddal in letters dated November 3, 2017 to Scotiabank and CIBC for living expenses for the months of September and October 2017. I believe only CIBC responded to the request of our counsel and I only received living expenses of $3,100.00 for September 2017. Attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of correspondence of Kieran Siddal to the financial institutions.</P>
<P>12. For the months of Decembers 2017 to December 2018, the calculations of San Chanshowth at neither I nor my husband used more than the permissible amount of $7,000 from any of our accounts.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Health</EM></TI>
<P>13. <BOLD>I</BOLD> have reviewed Affidavit #4 of Sarah Culver dated February 12, 2019 and can advises that the letters dated by Dr. Leslie Zypchen of December 17, 2018, Dr. Monica Brunner of December 18, 2018, Dr. Deborah Hocking of December 19, 2018, and Dr. Caroline Diana Condon dated January 17, 2019 were provided to me following assessment and treatment by each doctor on the date of the letter.</P>
<P>14. I am still suffering from the symptoms as contained in the letters of my doctors. The fatigue, vertigo, lightheadedness, shortness of breath, palpitations, and difficulty hearing continue to bother me and that I agree with my doctors that despite my willingness to do so, I am unable to endure an examination for discovery.</P>
<P>15. I consider my personal health a private matter and consider it a violation of my privacy for the plaintiff to enquire about more specifics beyond those contained in the letters of my physicians.</P>
<P>16. I confirm that I have surgery on February 22, 2019. I am not certain as to the recovery period for that surgery.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Discovery</EM></TI>
<P>17. I have reviewed my affidavit #1 in this matter and confirm the facts sworn to remain true.</P>
