<BLOCK1><TI><UNDER>AFFIDAVIT</UNDER></TI>
<P>I, <BOLD>JOHN HILPERT</BOLD>, private investigator, of 547 - 1917 West 4<SUP>th</SUP> Avenue, Vancouver, Province of British Columbia, MAKE OATH AND SAY AS FOLLOWS:</P>
<P>1. I am a private investigator retained by the plaintiff, Rong Wei, and as such have personal knowledge of the facts deposed to in this affidavit except where stated to be on information and belief and in which case I verily believe them to be true.</P>
<P>2. As I have explained in my previous affidavits, I was hired by Ms. Wei in November 2016 to look into the defendant Allan Chiu to verify his identity and certain claims he had made to Ms. Wei regarding his past.</P>
<P>3. In my first affidavit made on May 12, 2017, I referred in connection with my investigation of Mr. Chiu to Stoneset Equities and the Stoneset group of companies.</P>
<P>4. A copy of Mr. Chiu's business card that I obtained during my investigation is doublesided. One side of Mr. Chiu's business card lists &ldquo;Stoneset Equities&rdquo; and contains a distinct corporate logo. Underneath the name &ldquo;Stoneset Equities&rdquo;, the business card lists Calgary, Vancouver, Saskatoon, Toronto, Singapore and Dubai. Singapore is identified in a Stoneset Equities promotional video published in September 2010 for a property referred to as &ldquo;Vista Del Lago&rdquo; located in Invermere, British Columbia that can be accessed on youtube at the following address: <UNDER>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fmAdd3AkDis</UNDER>.</P>
<P>5. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is a screenshot of the 1.57 minute mark of the promotional video, which is a map identifying Singapore and the location of Vista Del Lago.</P>
<P>6. On the other side of the business card is Mr. Chiu's name, identified as a Director of Stoneset Equities Asia Pte. Ltd. and provides an address in Singapore, an email with the domain &ldquo;@stoneesetequities.com.sg&rdquo; and a reference to a website with the following web domain: stonesetequities.com.sg. During my investigation, I researched the historical website page identified on Mr. Chiu's business card and learned it was not registered as its own URL. Instead, the web address would take a person directly to the Stoneset website.</P>
<P>7. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is a copy of Mr. Chiu's business card.</P>
<P>8. The corporate logo located on the front side of Mr. Chiu's business card, as well as an image of a tree being reflected off a glass building on the second side of Mr. Chiu's business card, are both images that appear on a Stoneset brochure published in 2010-2011. Pages 4-5 of the brochure identify a location in Calgary as the &ldquo;Stoneset Head Office&rdquo;.</P>
<P>9. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is a copy of the brochure.</P>
<P>10. I am aware that a question has arisen about the document attached as Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo; to my first affidavit and, in particular, the listing on that document of Stoneset [Asia]. As part of my investigation I visited the Alberta Investors Protection website on a number of occasions and reprinted the article including the referenced list more than once. I made annotations on one or more print-outs as my investigation proceeded. Looking back now, some two years later, I believe that the wrong document was attached to my affidavit.</P>
<P>11. What appears as Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo; was a reference tool for me as I investigated the name association involving Stoneset, Stoneset Asia and Mr. Chiu. That reference tool appears to have been left in play as the exhibit, which I did not notice at the time I swore the affidavit. That was inadvertent on my part.</P>
<P>12. The document referenced in my affidavit as Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo; looked similar enough to the other webpages printed that list Stoneset Equities that I did not notice it was not from the website. For instance, a copy of the list naming &ldquo;Stoneset Equities&rdquo; from the Alberta Investor Protection website was included as Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo; to my first affidavit.</P>
