<BLOCK1><TI>AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, Allan Chiu, presently with no permanent address but with an address for service in this matter of 700-595 Burrard Street, Vancouver British Columbia, SWEAR THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am the husband of the Co-Defendant, Mui Kwan Queenie Lau, and am a personally named defendant in these proceedings and, as such, have personal knowledge of the facts and matters set out herein to this Affidavit, except where the same are stated to be on information and belief and, as to those matters, I verily believe them to be true.</P>
<P>2. At paragraph 87 of Affidavit of Rong Wei #1, Ms. Wei stated that I gave her a business card in November 2016. I did not give Ms. Wei the business card and am unaware as to how it came into her possession. As already has been stated in previous affidavits, I was retired from all business as of 2010.</P>
<P>3. At paragraphs 14&ndash;20 of Affidavit of Rong Wei #1, the Plaintiff stated that funds had been provided to purchase a TRU IPO shares. While the Plaintiff and I had discussions about the TRU IPO shares, they could not be purchased using the Wood Gundy trading account, which subsequently became CIBC Investor's Edge. The Plaintiff was aware of this. Ms. Wei did not provide any instructions to me at any time to purchase TRU IPO shares, or any shares excepting those regularly traded through the plaintiff's trading accounts.</P>
<P>4. At paragraphs 25&ndash;36 of Affidavit of Rong Wei #1, the Plaintiff stated that funds had been provided for the purchase of RACE IPO shares. Ms. Wei did not provide any instruction to me at any time to purchase RACE IPO shares, or any shares excepting those regularly traded through the plaintiff's trading accounts.</P>
<P>5. At paragraphs 37&ndash;45 of Affidavit of Rong Wei #1, the Plaintiff stated that funds had been provided for investment in Airbnb. Ms. Wei did not provide any instruction to me at any time to invest in Airbnb, or any shares excepting those regularly traded through the plaintiff's trading accounts.</P>
<P>6. At paragraphs 47-48 of Affidavit of Rong Wei #1, Ms. Wei states that she provided funds for investment in the UK Equities market. Ms. Wei provided funds generally for the purpose of potential investments in Europe which may include UK Investments but the funds were not particularized for UK Equities. The pattern of the Plaintiff was to deposit funds but not give instructions as to what was to be done with the funds. Additionally, the plaintiff references at Exhibit &ldquo;S&rdquo; a document purporting to be a summary that I provided. Ms. Wei did not provide any instruction to me at any time to invest in UK Equities, or any shares excepting those regularly traded through the plaintiff's trading accounts. As I deposed previously, I did not create and had not seen the document until seeing the document in the affidavit of Ms. Wei. I reference the statement of a UK Equities Portfolio Value as contained at Exhibit S, as it is my understanding that UK Equities cannot be traded in the CIBC Investor's Edge account.</P>
