<BLOCK1><TI>AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, Allan Chiu, presently with no permanent address but with an address for service in this matter of 700-595 Burrard Street, Vancouver British Columbia, SWEAR THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am the husband of the Co-Defendant, Mui Kwan Queenie Lau, and am a personally named defendant in these proceedings and, as such, have personal knowledge of the facts and matters set out herein to this Affidavit, except where the same are stated to be on information and belief and, as to those matters, I verily believe them to be true.</P>
<P>2. I am aware of the Order of Justice Humphries of May 18, 2017 in which paragraph 4 prohibits my wife and I from spending more than $25,000 each for legal fees and further that my wife and I are to advise the plaintiff in writing of the intended source of t he funds.</P>
<P>3. We have brought an application that alleges the Mareva Order was attained by the plaintiff through misrepresentation and material non-disclosure.</P>
<P>4. I can advise that my wife and I have funds owing with my current counsel and previous counsel, Kieran Siddall, for legal services and have not been able to satisfy those accounts.</P>
<P>5. I have been advised and verily believe it to be true that Mr. Driver, and my previous counsel Mr. Siddal, have advised the plaintiff through her counsel of the existence of a &ldquo;white knight&rdquo; who has provided funds, and has capacity, to provide further funds. However, I have instructed my counsel not to provide the white knight's name to anyone.</P>
<P>6. I am aware the Plaintiff has retained private investigators to surveil my wife and I between the dates of November 2016 to the present in Canada. I am also aware of private investigators being retained by the plaintiff in Singapore and Hong Kong. I am concerned of private investigators following and sureveilling the &ldquo;white knight&rdquo; and do not wish to subject that individual to the level of scrutiny both I and my wife have endured.</P>
<P>7. As such, I do not wish to identify the &ldquo;white knight&rdquo; who is providing their personal funds to defend this matter. The &ldquo;white knight&rdquo; does not reside in Canada.</P>
<P>8. We started to receive funds from the white knight on or about August, 2017 as a result of all funds being frozen. Since September, 2017, funds received from the white knight have been deposited into my wife's Bank of Montreal account.</P>
<P>9. At times, when I was unable to receive funds from the white knight, I would remove funds from my Standard Chartered Account in Singapore and deposit funds in my wife's Bank of Montreal account.</P>
<P>10. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> to this affidavit is an email chain initiated by CIBC on November 3, 2017 in response to a letter of my former counsel regarding the release of $3,500 from my wife's CIBC account and the confirmation from plaintiff counsel that the release of funds was not a violation of the Mareva order.</P>
<P>11. I swear this affidavit in response to the Notice of Application of the plaintiff in the above referenced action dated January 31, 2019 regarding discharge or variance of a Mareva Order.</P>
