<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, Allan Chiu, presently with no permanent address but with an address for service in this matter of 700 - 595 Burrard Street, Vancouver British Columbia, SWEAR THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am the husband of the Co-Defendant, Mui Kwan Queenie Lau, and am a personally named defendant in these proceedings and, as such, have personal knowledge of the facts and matters set out herein to this Affidavit, except where the same are stated to be on information and belief and, as to those matters, I verily believe them to be true.</P>
<P>2. Ms. Wei provided me a copy of her Bank of Montreal bank statement. The bank record was provided to me to explain how underground banking from China works. Ms. Wei advised me that the deposits contained on March 9, of a year I am unable to recall, of approximately $50,000 were from individuals unknown to her. Ms. Wei told me that the individuals were part of the underground banking system and that the amount of funds delivered were of a relatively small amount to avoid the attention Chinese authorities. Attached to this my affidavit as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> is a photograph of page 2 of 5 of Ms. Wei's Bank of Montreal account #XXXXXXXXXX.</P>
<P>3. In further reference to Exhibit A, 3 incoming wire transfers are delivered by a Li Huaixin, the plaintiff's former husband. Ms. Wei told me that Mr. Li used a higher level underground bank with more connections and wider networks to move greater than $2.5 million out of China.</P>
<P>4. On February 26, 2016, Ms. Wei advised me that she was intending to deliver funds to CIBC or AnXin accounts in a WeChat message. She advised that if she used underground banking that she can transfer money wherever it is preferred. As previously contained in my Affidavit #2 of this matter but additionally attached to this my 5<SUP>th</SUP> affidavit as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of that correspondence in the WeChat messages.</P>
<P>5. On March 7, 2016, Ms. Wei also advised me that she transferred funds to her Anxin account. Ms. Wei responded that she has used AnXin and underground banking and both were safe. As previously contained in my Affidavit #2 of this matter but additionally attached to this my 5<SUP>th</SUP> affidavit as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of that correspondence in the WeChat messages.</P>
<P>6. Around March 7, 2016, Ms. Wei additionally provided me a copy of the an Essence International Securities (Hong Kong) Limited bank account No. XXXXXXXXXX in the name of Xiang Wang, the Plaintiff's mother, for the period of March 2016. Ms. Wei told me that one of the uses for her mother's bank account was to transfer money using the Chinese underground banks. Further, she advised me that the deposits of $255,988.06-$255,988.07 (HKD) are examples of deposits from the Chinese underground bank system. Attached to this affidavit as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;D&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of Essence International Securities (Hong Kong) Limited bank account record provided to me by Ms. Wei.</P>
<P>7. Ms. Wei advised me that she had access to all funds in her mother's account referenced and, further, that her mother's account was the recipient of funds from unknown sources in China.</P>
<P>8. The delivered funds from underground banks were sent to this account and Ms. Wei's accounts in Canada.</P>
<P>9. I swear this affidavit in response to the Notice of Application of the plaintiff in the above referenced action to be heard on February 14, 2019 regarding the Mareva Order and an application for a preservation order.</P>
