<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="II">AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, Allan Chiu, resident of Metro Vancouver with an address for service in this matter of 700-595 Burrard Street, Vancouver British Columbia, SWEAR THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am the husband of the Co-Defendant, Mui Kwan Queenie Lau, and am a personally named defendant in these proceedings and, as such, have personal knowledge of the facts and matters set out herein to this Affidavit, except where the same are stated to be on information and belief and, as to those matters, I verily believe them to be true.</P>
<P>2. I am aware of my obligation to produce my financial records. As particularized in my Schedule of Assets attached as Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo; to my 1<SUP>st</SUP> Affidavit sworn June 21, 2017, I have had bank accounts with the following financial institutions:
<P1>(a) two accounts at Standard Chartered Bank, 1 Harbourfront Walk, Vivo City, Singapore which were:
<P2>(i) Xtrasaver SGD account #XXXXXXXXXX; and</P2>
<P2>(ii) FCYsaver USD account #XXXXXXXXXX.</P2>
(the &ldquo;Singapore Accounts&rdquo;)</P1>
<P1>(b) two accounts at Bank of China, 1 Garden Road, Central, Hong Kong which are:
<P2>(i) HKD Savings account #XXXXXXXXXX and</P2>
<P2>(ii) MTC account #XXXXXXXXXX.</P2>
(the &ldquo;<BOLD>Hong Kong Accounts</BOLD>&rdquo;)</P1></P>
<P>3. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> is this affidavit is my 1<SUP>st</SUP> Affidavit sworn June 21, 2017.</P>
<P>4. With respect to the Singapore Accounts, I was advised by way of letter dated July 6, 2018 from Standard Chartered Bank that the Singapore Accounts were closed effective September 6, 2018. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> is a letter I received from Yap Jee Hoe, Regional Head, CDD Operations for Standard Chartered Bank (Singapore) Limited (&ldquo;<BOLD>Standard Chartered Singapore</BOLD>&rdquo;) dated July 6, 2018.</P>
<P>5. My counsel has advised me, and I verily believe it to be true, that records for the Singapore Accounts have been provided to the plaintiff for the period January 22, 2016 to July 21, 2018. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of the produced Singapore Account records.</P>
<P>6. I have personally attended to requesting all bank records for the Standard Chartered Account. In response, I received an email from &ldquo;Saras&rdquo; a Client Care Executive with Standard Chartered Singapore dated February 14, 2019 attached to which were the records contained at Exhibit C to this affidavit. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;D&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of the email dated February 14, 2019 from Saras.</P>
<P>7. I have personally made numerous phone calls to XXXXXXXXXX before the records that were provided in the email dated February 14, 2019 referenced at paragraph 6 and after. After February 14, 2019, I have continued to call Standard Chartered Singapore to request records for the period May 2015 to December 2015. My most recent follow-up phone call with Zrin on April 2 at approximately 11 pm (PST) to Standard Chartered Singapore advised me that I should receive the additional statements in approximately 3 days.</P>
<P>8. With respect to the Hong Kong Accounts, I contacted the Bank of China in Hong Kong to request records. I was advised that the bank was unable to provide records because of a restriction noted on the file related to the Hong Kong Accounts.</P>
<P>9. I am advised, and verily believe it to be true, that my counsel has attempted to contact the Bank of China in Hong Kong by letter on my behalf.</P>
<P>10. I understand the importance of fully complying with the court order of Madam J Dillon, and I am very sorry for the delay in obtaining the financial documents, and I am continuing my efforts to obtain the records that must be produced.</P>
<P>11. I write this affidavit in support of an order requiring the 3<SUP>rd</SUP> parties to produce all of the financial records that I have been unable to secure on my own.</P>
