<P>4. With respect to the accounts at paragraph 3 of this affidavit, I provided through my counsel all financial records from June 1, 2015 to present for:
<P1>(a) all accounts at the Bank of Montreal; and</P1>
<P1>(b) BMW Finance.</P1></P>
<P>5. With respect to the accounts at paragraph 3 of this affidavit, I provided through my counsel all financial records from June 1, 2015 to December 12, 2018;
<P1>(a) all accounts at CIBC; and</P1>
<P1>(b) all accounts at Scotiabank.</P1></P>
<P>6. I have been advised and verily believe it to be true that my counsel has requested the remaining two months of records from CIBC and Scotiabank.</P>
<P>7. With respect to the accounts at paragraph 3 of this affidavit, I provided through my counsel the records from November 22, 2017 to February, 2019 for my Costco Credit Card.</P>
<P>8. I have personally made numerous calls to the customer service number 1 -800-723-3500 between March 11, 2019 to today's date. Initially, I was informed the records can only be retrieved for 18 months prior to the date they are produced. However, I insisted I receive records from June 1, 2015. During a phone call with an employee or service agent named Paul at 11: 53 a.m. on April 1, 2019, he confirmed my request for statements was in progress and the statements should arrive in approximately 21 days.</P>
<P>9. With respect to the accounts at paragraph 3 of this affidavit, I provided through my counsel the records from November 25, 2017 to October 24, 2018 for my Hudson's Bay Credit Card.</P>
<P>10. I have personally made numerous calls to the customer service number 1 -866-640-7858 between March 11, 2019 to today's date. Initially, I was informed the records can only be retrieved for 12 months prior to the date they are produced. However, I insisted I receive records from June 1, 2015. During a phone call with an employee or service agent named Fouzan on April 1, 2019, he confirmed that the records would be produced from June 1, 2015 to present. I was not provided an estimated time for the records to arrive.</P>
<P>11. With respect to the accounts at paragraph 3 of this affidavit, I have been unable to secure financial records from Toronto Dominion Bank.</P>
<P>12. I have been advised and verily believe it to be true that my counsel has delivered letters requesting records from Toronto Dominion Bank. I have been advised that Toronto Dominion Bank has not responded to the requests.</P>
<P>13. I have reviewed affidavit #5 of Sarah Culver and verily believe it to be true that my counsel have delivered letters requesting records from Standard Chartered Bank in Hong Kong.</P>
<P>14. In addition to the written requests, I have called the customer service number of 852 -2886-8866 on numerous occasions between March 10, 2019 to today's date. During a phone call with an employee or service agents, I was consistently provided the statement that the account was frozen and the bank could not entertain any request from the account holder. The only agent that would provide his name was Mr. Sin at extension 55987, who confirmed the bank would not entertain a request from the account holder during a phone call on March 31, 2019.</P>
<P>15. I understand that my efforts to obtain the Standard Chartered Bank financial records have been successful, because today I was advised by my counsel that Standard Chartered Bank has advised that the records are ready for pick-up but a fee has to be paid. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of a letter received by my counsel today, from Standard Chartered.</P>
<P>16. I understand the importance of fully complying with the court order of Madam J Dillon, I have been fully focussed on taking all steps within my abilities and control to fully comply with each and every term of the order. I am apologetic that there has been delay on the part of 3<SUP>rd</SUP> parties as it relates to production and compliance with the order.</P>
<P>17. I write this affidavit in support of an order requiring the 3<SUP>rd</SUP> parties to produce all of the financial records that I have been unable to secure on my own.</P>
